org.ensor.robots.scheduler

Class Event

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ensor.robots.primitives.Atom
      • org.ensor.robots.primitives.DictionaryAtom
        • org.ensor.robots.scheduler.Event
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    JSONSerializable, URLSerializable

    public class Event
extends DictionaryAtom
implements JSONSerializable
    An Event is a dictionary with a name. These are primarily used as the primitive event data type. Data can be placed into the property tree with a given name and simply 'sent' to another Biote through Biote.sendStimulus(int, org.ensor.robots.scheduler.Event). An event can be created directly from a JSON Object, from a given dictionary, or can be constructed as an empty dictionary and values can be added after the fact.

    Jon
